document.heading: Omnibus Budget Support Temporary Act of 1992

history.narrative: Law 9-134, the “Omnibus Budget Support Temporary Act of 1992,” was introduced in Council and assigned Bill No. 9-485. The Bill was adopted on first and second readings on April 7, 1992, and May 6, 1992, respectively. Approved without the signature of the Mayor on May 29, 1992, it was assigned Act No. 9-219 and transmitted to both Houses of Congress for its review. D.C. Law 9-134 became effective on July 23, 1992.
